Package org.ejbca.ui.web.admin.audit

Class AuditorManagedBean

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ejbca.ui.web.admin.audit.AuditorManagedBean
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    public class AuditorManagedBean
extends Object
implements Serializable
    JSF Backing bean for viewing security audit logs. Reloads the data lazily if when requested if something was cause for an update (first time, user has invoked reload etc). getConditions() will handle special cases when HTTP GET parameters are passed (e.g. show history for a username).
    Version:
    $Id: AuditorManagedBean.java 28844 2018-05-04 08:31:02Z samuellb $

        public Map<String,​Integer> getStringTooLong()
        Ugly hack to be able to read the length of the resulting String from JSF EL. Example: "#{auditor.stringTooLong[(auditLogEntry.mapAdditionalDetails)] > 50}" TODO: Use javax.faces.model.DataModel instead
        Returns:
        a fake "Map" where the get(Map) returns the length of the output-formatted Map
